The secret of splendor over Norway solved: the Russians tested a missile
A special light effect of unknown origin was observed over Norway.
The Russian Ministry of Defense ended up acknowledging yesterday that near the borders with Norway it had tested an intercontinental ballistic missile.
The launch failed again. The &quot;Bulava&quot;-type missile, once meant to be the pride of the Russian military, is becoming the bane of Russian generals and Prime Minister Vladimír Putin.
Even their repeated presence in missile tests has not had the desired effect on the success of the test flights.
Bulavá, in most cases, either did not fly or failed in the air.
In Russian newspapers they write about &quot;Bulava&quot; as &quot;a missile that does not fly&quot;.
A missile that does not fly, but shines.
During this, the 13th test, there were no problems at first.
At the end of the flight there were again technical problems in the device.
The engine probably blew up in the third stage of the missile.
This time &quot;Bulava&quot; was launched from the nuclear submarine Dmitry Donskoy, which was floating submerged in the White Sea.
This type of missile makes it possible to launch from a vessel that is moving and is submerged at the same time.
That is why it is likely that the mysterious light over Norway, caused by an unidentified flying object, was actually the failed &quot;Bulavá&quot;.
The Norwegians also from the first moment did not hesitate that it was a Russian missile.
The generals this time defend themselves by stating that one cannot simply speak of failure.
The first two stages of the missile held, and the failure occurred in the third.
In the above cases the engines failed immediately in the first stage.
Although none of the launches was completely without errors, according to the Ministry of Defense, only six of the thirteen were unsuccessful.
The success of almost fifty percent fills the generals with optimism and for this reason they continue to affirm that &quot;Bulavá&quot; will one day fly without problems and that it will even manage to carry up to ten nuclear hypersonic blocks, the maximum total weight of which is 1.15 tons.
