Employees can collect the bonus for overtime or take a day off on December 28, that is, extend the Christmas holidays by one day, Vaněk said.
In addition, all employees on Saturday shifts will receive travel and meal money.
As the overtime work was the most urgent and problematic point of comments and complaints from trade unionists and strikers, who stopped manufacturing last week, the management decided yesterday afternoon to immediately cancel all overtime work for the month of December. Vaněk mentioned.
Employees at the car factory were forced to work two more hours on top of eight-hour shifts, and this situation continued almost every day until last week.
After signing the agreement the unions will cancel the emergency strike.
