They also protested against the bad payment conditions and the alleged harassment.
Management felt that employees had to work overtime to meet the requirements to supply the cars.
The unionists, in their declaration of the emergency due to strike on Monday, also demanded that none of the employees, who interrupted manufacturing last Wednesday, be penalized in any way.
As far as additional work is concerned, the unions demand that the company reduce it to a minimum.
In addition, this year they require a remuneration of 5,000 crowns for this work.
The automobile factory in Nošovice Hyundai currently has 2,000 employees.
Serial production began last November.
Until last September, it manufactured approximately 80,000 cars; its current productive potential is 200,000 cars a year.
