It shows the outlines for a possible deal, in which industrialized nations would collectively cut their 2020 emissions by 25 to 45 percent, compared to 1990 levels, while major developing countries would cut theirs over the same period. period between 15 and 30 percent.
Together, the countries would cut emissions between 50 and 95 percent by 2050.
The European Union also spurred talks on Friday, pledging to provide $3.6 billion a year for the next three years to help the poorest countries adapt to the impact of climate change, from floods and droughts to deforestation.
