Michelin and Fesvial together for the use of the helmet
The tire manufacturer Michelin, with the collaboration of the Spanish Foundation for Road Safety (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the use of helmets, mainly among the youngest motorcyclists, both entities reported today.
This initiative seeks to raise awareness about the importance of wearing a helmet, since it is the only element of protection capable of avoiding head injuries or even death in the event of an accident while riding a motorcycle.
Michelin indicated that this campaign is part of its commitment to road safety, which &quot;goes beyond designing and manufacturing products that are safer every day&quot; and affirmed that it also contributes to this goal through other educational and informative actions.
