The acceleration capacity is brutal, either from a standstill or recoveries.
The suspensions are firm, but not harsh or uncomfortable.
The asphalt of the roads that we crossed with the Boxster Spyder was quite punished, but the car digested the potholes well.
The electronic aids barely made an appearance throughout the journey; and that in some of the curves we found ice at dawn and gravel, well into the morning.
In short, an ultralight car, one of the most fun to drive on the market and that is more than a simple modification of the Boxster S.
