How much should you charge for your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can find out the salary they deserve according to their profile, thanks to a new Trovit application, the search engine with the largest number of real estate, employment and motor classified ads in Spain.
The tool How much should you charge? calculates the salaries of users from the more than 140,000 job offers that Trovit has in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where they must enter their profession, years of experience, age and city where they want to work.
In the week that the application has been running, the search engine has detected that, in general terms, the Spanish worker &quot;feels poorly paid,&quot; Trovit&#39;s product manager, Albert Ribera, explained in a statement.
According to the data available to Trovit from its search engines in the United Kingdom and France, the Spanish are the worst paid.
A British computer programmer earns 45,226 euros gross per year and a French one, 31,059, compared to the 24,000 that a Spanish one receives.
In the same way, a driver earns 34,247 euros net per year in England, 25,751 in France and 16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest paid job in Spain is that of a waiter, with 11,592 euros net per year; followed by the dependent, with 14,725 euros; and that of operator, with 15,667 euros.
The jobs most sought after on the web in the last three months are drivers, part-time jobs and social workers.
